				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">You could try dividing your SDL screen into panes. Open a 1024x600 pixel window (I chose this size so that it'd be full screen on a small laptop) and then, within your app, split it into two panes: the left 592x480* for the emulated console's screen, and the remaining 432 pixels for any debugger.
<br />
<br />
<br /><span style="font-size: 84%; line-height: normal">* Why not 512x480? Pixel aspect ratio. At the NES's dot clock rate, a 4:3 screen would be 280x240 pixels. If you enlarge a 259x240 pixel display (including 3 columns of side border in color 0) to 592x480 square pixels, it'll have the right PAR.</span></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

